parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Lock Cylinder Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and lock cylinder can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and become difficult or impossible to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the ignition switch fails to turn
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the steering wheel locks
the air bag and ABS warning indicators illuminate
and the vehicle is unable to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, and become difficult or impossible to start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
loses power
or becomes difficult to start
the air bag and ABS warning indicators illuminate
and the vehicle experiences electrical shorts or burning odors.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power seat can cause electrical shorts, burning odors, and potentially lead to a fire, which can cause injuries or damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The power seat moves independently
and electrical shorts or burning odors are present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the windows to malfunction, which can lead to safety issues and inconvenience.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure in Rainy Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system in rainy conditions can cause the vehicle to be difficult or impossible to steer, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The power steering system fails or becomes difficult to operate when driving in rainy or wet road conditions
especially when making right-hand turns or driving at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wheel lock-up can cause the vehicle to be difficult or impossible to steer, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult or impossible to turn
especially when making right-hand turns or driving at slow speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
especially when driving in rainy or wet road conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window regulator can cause the window to fall into the door, making it difficult or impossible to operate, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The window falls into the door

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sun roof glass can cause the glass to shatter or detach from the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the mirror adjusters and console can cause distraction while driving, which can lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended air bag deployment can cause injuries, distractions, and accidents, potentially leading to serious consequences.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of air bags to deploy in a crash can lead to increased risk of injury or fatality.
